About This

This web page is dedicated to the realization that cheesecake is awesome. Cheesecake is like the pizza of desert. It even comes in your typical circle/pie shape like pizza! This isn't about pizza though, this is about cheesecake. Have you ever tried Cheesecake? If so, what is your favorite kind? Ours is Oreo Cheesecake. That being said, there is an Oreo Cheesecake recipe that is featured for this page. Enjoy this cheesecake web page.

Oreo Cheesecake (is the best) recipe

2 pkg. (8 oz. each) brick cream cheese, softened
1/2 cup sugar
1/2 tsp. vanilla
2 eggs
6 OREO Cookies, coarsely chopped, divided,
1 OREO Pie Crust (6 oz.)

Instructions:
HEAT oven to 325 degrees F.
BEAT cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer until blended. Add eggs; mix just until blended. Stir in 1/2 cup cookies.
POUR into crust; sprinkle with remaining cookies.
BAKE 35 to 40 min. or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours.

History of New York Cheesecake

1929 â€“ Arnold Reuben, owner of the legendary Turf Restaurant at 49th and Broadway in New York City, claimed that his family developed the first cream-cheese cake recipe. Other bakeries relied on cottage cheese. According to legend, he was served a cheese pie in a private home, and he fell in love with the dessert. Using his hostess recipe and a pie she made with ingredients he provided, he then began to develop his own recipe for the perfect cheesecake. Reuben soon began to serve his new recipe in his Turf Restaurant, and the cheesecake quickly became very popular with the people who frequented Reubens Broadway restaurant.
